      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI SING (9) impressed when fresh from a spell last time out, racing parked before digging deep and getting home by 3 metres at Wagga. Draws on the back row this time but should strip fitter and won over this distance the only time he raced here. MAJOR BLITZ (8) made it three from three so far this campaign when overcoming another wide barrier to lead and score by 4.2m at Bendigo. Too good in his only visit to this circuit prior. Draws on the back row this time but winning form is tough to knock. KEAYANG PAYTON (3) should find this easier than the last attempt and did well to win at Melton prior. Draws for a good showing. THE STEEL DRAGON (7) draws wide but came from the back row to salute at Bendigo last week and owns a strong record here.",
